For my Beautiful Sweet Bebbe

Before you, love was just a word I knew,
A passing thought, a distant view.
But then you walked into my days,
And turned my ordinary into always.

You don't just make my world feel bright
You are the sun, the stars, the light.
In your arms, I've found my place,
My safest home, my favorite space.

Your voice quiets every fear,
Your heartbeat is the rhythm I hear.
If love is a lifetime, here's my start
Every tomorrow, you have my heart.

So this Valentine's, I ask you
Keep choosing me like I choose you.

Forever and Always

If I could give you anything,
It wouldn't be flowers that fade in spring.
I'd give you mornings wrapped in peace,
And every worry gently cease.

I'd give you strength on your hardest days,
A steady hand when life sways.
I'd give you laughter that never ends,
A love that deepens, never bends.

Because loving you isn't something I do
It's who I am when I'm with you.
You're not just my Valentine for a day,
You're my forever

My Promise to You

I promise to always make you smile,
To walk with you every single mile.
To hold your hand through thick and thin,
To celebrate every loss and win.

I promise to listen when you need to talk,
To be there for every midnight walk.
To support your dreams, both big and small,
To catch you every time you fall.

I promise to love you more each day,
In every single possible way.
To be your partner, your best friend too,
Forever and always, it's me and you.

What You Mean to Me

You're my sunshine on the cloudiest days,
My guiding light in so many ways.
You make me laugh when I want to cry,
You're the reason I reach for the sky.

With you, I've found my safest place,
In your arms, in your sweet embrace.
You're my today and my tomorrow,
My joy in happiness, my comfort in sorrow.

So here's my promise, forever true
I'll spend my life loving only you.
